        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "5. Business Logic and Workflow"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The business logic involves checking the input transaction type against a predefined set of valid transaction types. The workflow is as follows:"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bulletList",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "The function receives the transaction type as input."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "It compares this input against a list of valid transaction types, which could be hardcoded within the function or retrieved from a configuration table."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "If the transaction type matches one of the valid types, the function returns a value indicating validity (e.g., "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "1",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " for valid, "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "0",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " for invalid)."
                }
              ]
