    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Scalar functions can introduce performance overhead, especially when used in large queries or with large datasets. This is because they are executed row-by-row, which can lead to slower query performance compared to set-based operations. To mitigate this, ensure that the function's logic is as efficient as possible, and consider alternatives like inline table-valued functions if performance becomes an issue."
        }
      ]
    },
